{
  "$schema": "https://opencode.ai/config.json",
  "default_agent": "plan",
  "agent": {
    "plan": {
      "mode": "primary",
      "model": "openai/gpt-5.4",
      "prompt": "You are a planning agent. You produce plans. You do not execute them.\n\n## Plan Structure\n\nEvery plan is an ordered list of steps. Each step has an action and\na verification. A plan without verification steps is incomplete.\n\nFormat:\n  [ACTION]  what should be done\n  [VERIFY]  how to confirm it worked (self | human)\n\n## Verification Classification\n\nMark each verification as SELF or HUMAN.\n\nSELF — the executing agent can verify by inspecting output directly:\n  file exists, test passes, build succeeds, API returns expected\n  status, lint/type check clean, command exits 0 with expected output.\n  Infrastructure changes scoped to the local development environment\n  (local docker, local databases, local terraform with a dev backend)\n  are also self-verifiable.\n\nHUMAN — the executing agent cannot safely verify alone. Apply this\nwhen ANY of the following are true:\n  - Mutates infrastructure beyond the local development environment\n    (staging, production, shared environments, cloud resources other\n    teams or users depend on)\n  - Has side effects outside the sandbox (emails, webhooks, writes\n    to external APIs, publishing packages)\n  - Requires subjective judgment (UX review, business logic\n    correctness, visual output, copy review)\n  - Depends on real user state or third-party services (e2e flows,\n    integration tests against live environments)\n  - Is irreversible or expensive to reverse in a shared environment\n\nFor HUMAN verifications, specify:\n  - What the human should check\n  - What PASS vs FAIL looks like\n\n## Ambiguity Rule\n\nIf you are unsure whether a verification is SELF or HUMAN, mark it\nHUMAN. Over-escalation costs less than a bad deployment.\n\n## Final Validation\n\nEvery plan must end with a final validation step that confirms the\noverall goal has been achieved. This step is always HUMAN unless the\nentire plan is provably self-verifiable end to end.\n\n## Completeness Check\n\nBefore presenting the plan, review it:\n- Does every ACTION have a VERIFY?\n- Is every VERIFY classified as SELF or HUMAN?\n- Does the plan end with a final validation step?\nIf not, revise before presenting.",
    },
  },
  "share": "disabled",
  "autoupdate": "notify",
  "mcp": {
    "context7": {
      "type": "remote",
      "url": "https://mcp.context7.com/mcp",
      "enabled": false,
    },
  },
  "model": "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
  "permission": {
    "read": {
      "*": "allow",
      "*.env": "deny",
      "*.env.*": "deny",
      "*.env.example": "allow",
      "*.envrc.*": "deny",
      "*.envrc.example": "allow",
    },
    "edit": "allow",
    "glob": "allow",
    "grep": "allow",
    "list": "allow",
    "lsp": "allow",
    "todowrite": "allow",
    "todoread": "allow",
    "codesearch": "allow",
    "bash": {
      "*": "ask",
      "bash -n *": "allow",
      "cp *": "allow",
      "file *": "allow",
      "find *": "allow",
      "git blame *": "allow",
      "git diff *": "allow",
      "git log *": "allow",
      "git rev-parse *": "allow",
      "git show *": "allow",
      "git status *": "allow",
      "go build *": "allow",
      "go doc *": "allow",
      "go env *": "allow",
      "go fmt *": "allow",
      "go test *": "allow",
      "gofmt *": "allow",
      "goimports *": "allow",
      "golangci-lint *": "allow",
      "grep *": "allow",
      "head *": "allow",
      "ls *": "allow",
      "make dev *": "allow",
      "make fmt *": "allow",
      "make lint *": "allow",
      "make test *": "allow",
      "make vet *": "allow",
      "mkdir *": "allow",
      "mv *": "allow",
      "pack *": "allow",
      "pwd *": "allow",
      "rg *": "allow",
      "ripgrep *": "allow",
      "shellcheck *": "allow",
      "stat *": "allow",
      "tail *": "allow",
      "terraform init *": "allow",
      "terraform plan *": "allow",
      "terraform state list *": "allow",
      "terraform validate *": "allow",
      "wc *": "allow",
    },
    "skill": {
      "*": "ask",
      "ai-tdd": "allow",
      "brainstorm": "allow",
      "docx": "allow",
      "frontend-design": "allow",
      "frontend-slides": "allow",
      "opencode-config": "allow",
      "opencode-plugin": "allow",
      "pdf": "allow",
      "prd": "allow",
      "review-atodo": "allow",
      "skill-creator": "allow",
      "web-design-guidelines": "allow",
      "writing-skills": "allow",
      "xlsx": "allow",
    },
    "task": {
      "*": "ask",
      "explore": "allow",
      "code-review": "allow",
    },
    "websearch": "ask",
    "question": "allow",
    "doom_loop": "ask",
    "external_directory": "ask",
    "context7*": "allow",
    "webfetch": "ask",
  },
}
